The '''Intruder missile''' was a special type of ordnance with a very strong ionizing effect used during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
The Intruder missile was originally designed by [[Slayn & Korpil/Legends|Slayn & Korpil]], most commonly known for its unique vehicle designs. The initial design was distributed to [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] and used aboard their [[A/SF-01 B-wing starfighter/Legends|B-Wing]] bombers as well as [[Z-95 Headhunter/Legends|Z-95 Headhunters]] and [[YT-series/Legends|YT-class freighters]]. [[File:IntruderMissile2.jpg|thumb|left|180px|A [[Sienar]]-produced Intruder Missile]] The missile is armed with an ionizing [[Warhead/Legends|warhead]] designed specifically to overload the [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|shield generators]] on [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]], causing them to explode and destroy the rest of the ship in the process. The missile was incapable of targeting anything smaller than [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]] and was much more effective if the target was being simultaneously attacked by other weapons&mdash;perhaps as a means of destabilizing the [[Deflector shield/Legends|shield generators]] or allowing the missile to penetrate the shields and impact the hull.<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Special Edition Limited|cardname=Intruder Missile (Dark)}}</ref>

In an unusual reversal of roles, [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|ISB]] agents stole the design from the Rebel-sympathizing Slayn & Korpil and gave the plans to [[Sienar]] to produce the weapon for them. Perhaps as a result of this theft, [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] acquired the missile to sell to bounty hunters and mercenaries. The Sienar-produced missile was more commonly loaded onto [[TIE/sa tactical bomber/Legends|TIE Bombers]], [[TIE/d "Defender" Multi-Role Starfighter/Legends|TIE Defenders]], and freighters than other [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] craft.<ref name="CCG" />

